subSubSection.paragraph:
The larvae of 

M. vandepolli

can be distinguished by the following characteristics, with those of 

D. borealis

given in parentheses: 
1
) endocarina well developed (endocarina absent); 
2
) abdominal segments I-VIII dorsally and ventrally with grooves (grooves absent); 
3
) ventral side of the abdominal segments I-VIII bearing two setae (with 
10
setae); 
4
) abdominal segment IX dorsally with four pairs of setae (with six pairs of setae).
